The `getRecords` function should then set the filter, page and/or page size. Something like this:

```js
function getRecords() {
  var $table = $('table'),
    filters = [];
  // update whichever column needs to be updated
  filters[2] = $("#DATSTAT").val();
  // update filters, but don't apply the search
  $.tablesorter.setFilters( $table, filters, false );
  // go back to page 1 with 20 entries per page
  $table.trigger("pageAndSize", [1, 20]);
}
```

If you're not using the filter to switch data sets, then use the `customAjaxUrl` callback function to alter the ajax url.

Ref:

* [`setFilters`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#function-setfilters)
* [`pageAndSize`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pageandsize)
* [`customAjaxUrl`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pager-customajaxurl)

